			<description><![CDATA[<p><strong>Summary </strong></p>
<p><a href="http://www.harqen.com/?utm_source=theResumator&amp;utm_medium=Web_Job_Boards&amp;utm_campaign=Test">HarQen</a> is looking for an entrepreneurial Controller / Director of Operations, a full time position for one of the most exciting start-up companies in the Milwaukee area. You would lead and coordinate of the company's financial planning, debt/equity financing as well as all budget management functions. You would ensure company accounting procedures conform to generally-accepted accounting principles. You would also be involved in the planning of key projects, and others, as listed below:</p>
<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Direct and coordinate company financial planning and budget management functions.</li>
<li>Recommend benchmarks for measuring the financial and operating performance of divisions and departments.</li>
<li>Maintain key banking relationships.</li>
<li>Work with bank to secure line of credit.</li>
<li>Monitor and analyze monthly operating results against budget.</li>
<li>Direct and coordinate debt financing and debt service payments with external agencies.</li>
<li>Oversee daily operations of the finance department.</li>
<li>Manage the preparation of the official annual report of actual revenues, transfers, and expenses.</li>
<li>Manage the preparation of financial outlooks and financial forecasts.</li>
<li>Prepare financial analysis for contract negotiations and product investment decisions.</li>
<li>Ensure compliance with local, state, and federal budgetary reporting requirements.</li>
<li>Work with department managers and corporate staff to develop five year and ten year business plans for the company.</li>
<li>Establish and implement short- and long-range departmental goals, objectives, policies, and operating procedures.</li>
<li>Design, establish, and maintain an organizational structure and staffing to effectively accomplish the department's goals and objectives.</li>
<li>Serve on planning and policy-making committees.</li>
<li>Direct financial audits and provide recommendations for procedural improvements.</li>
<li>Maintain and support the office environment (e.g., purchasing supplies, materials, and key licenses)</li>
<li>Coordinate representation of the company externally to media, government agencies, funding agencies, and the general public.</li>
<li>Manage HR responsibilities for the company, including background checks, new employee on-boarding (e.g., new equipment, furniture, access).</li>
<li>Respond to direct investor inquiries. •	Coordinate performance reviews for all team members.</li>
<li>Work with board to create and administer bonus plan.</li>
<li>Administer 401K and flexible spending accounts.</li>
<li>Collect and verify data for the corporate dashboard</li>
<li>Coordinate communications with the board of directors and investors, including compiling board book and investor newsletter, so that they are distributed in a timely fashion.</li>
<li>Provide accounting policy orientation for new staff.</li>
<li>Lead the planning for assigned projects and manage implementation.</li>
<li>Facilitate the definition of assigned project scope, goals and deliverables.</li>
<li>Define project tasks and resource requirements •	Develop full scale plans for assigned projects</li>
<li>Assemble and coordinate team members for assigned projects</li>
<li>Manage project budget</li>
<li>Manage project resource allocation</li>
<li>Plan and schedule project timelines</li>
<li>Track project deliverables using appropriate tools</li>
<li>Provide direction and support to project team</li>
<li>Provide quality assurance on assigned projects</li>
<li>Constantly monitor and report on progress of the project to all stakeholders</li>
<li>Present reports defining project progress, problems and solutions</li>
<li>Implement and manage project changes and interventions to achieve project outputs</li>
<li>Project evaluations and assessment of results</li>
<li>Preparation of non-financial information for monthly presentation to the Board of Directors meeting</li>
<li>Compensation and Benefits administration<br /> Employee On-boarding and Payroll administration<br /> Calendaring and travel arrangements <br /> Purchasing of office equipment, supplies and vendor management<br /> Liaison with office building staff and maintenance</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Qualifications</strong></p>
<p>•	Bachelor’s degree</p>
<p>•	3-7 years experience in accounting / finance  Salary/Benefits:  Salary commensurate with experience:</p>
<p>We offer flexible benefits and compensation packages that allow our employees to make choices that fit their individual lifestyles.</p>
<p>Some of the benefits for full-time employees include the following: •	Health Insurance •	401K •	Minimum 15 days flexible time off, additional sick time, plus 10 paid holidays.</p>
